Digitaria exilis

   [5329.jpg]
   Authority (Kippist) Stapf
   Family Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
   Synonyms Paspalum exile Kippist, Panicum exile (Kippist) A. Chev.,
   Syntherisma exilis (Kippist) Newbold
   Common names fonio, white fonio, hungry rice, hungry millet, hungry
   koos, fundi millet, fonio du Sénégal, petit mil, fini, acha,
   cereals-fonio, findo
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 5329

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION An erect, free-tillering grass and cereal crop
   reaching a height of about 45 cm. USES The small grain contains about
   80% carbohydrates and 10% protein. It is made into porridge, ground and
   mixed with other cereals, or used in the brewing of beer. The straw can
   be used as fodder. GROWING PERIOD Annual. Reach maturity in 90-130 days
   depending on culitvar. The crop is sown during June and July, and
   harvested in September and October. COMMON NAMES Hungry rice, Fonio,
   Fundi, Acha. FURTHER INF Hungry rice is considered native of West
   Africa, and is grown throughout the savanna areas from Senegal to
   Cameroun. Yields vary from 150-800 kg/ha, but over 1 t/ha have been
   recorded.

   Sources
   SOURCES (D. exilis (Kippist) Stapf)
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 143-144 [RAIN, USE, FER, DEP, DRA]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 34 [USE]
   Duke J 1979 pp 95 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]

